parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the vehicle to emit excessive pollutants, leading to environmental harm and potential health risks. In addition, the faulty converter can cause the check engine warning light to appear, which can lead to further engine damage if ignored.
symptoms: Check engine warning light appears on the dashboard
catalytic converter not burning up exhaust gases properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine lifter can cause the engine to shake, leading to loss of control and potential accidents. It can also cause excessive engine noise and damage to other engine components.
symptoms: Vehicle shakes while driving
fumes come out from the exhaust
check engine warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Oil Leaks and Low Oil Levels
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Low engine oil levels can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potential engine failure. This can also lead to accidents if the engine seizes while driving.
symptoms: Engine sounds weird
like it's low on engine oil
engine oil levels are consistently low despite regular oil changes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility while driving, leading to accidents and potential harm to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Windshield wipers stop working
especially in rainy or wet conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Auto START/STOP feature can cause the vehicle to stall unexpectedly, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents, especially when stopping at red lights or driving on highways.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while driving
the message to restart the vehicle is displayed
the vehicle requires shifting into park or neutral before restarting
the failure occurs intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling while driving can cause a loss of control and potential accidents, especially when driving at high speeds on highways.
symptoms: The vehicle turns off while driving
the vehicle will not turn back on
the failure occurs suddenly and without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Telecommunication Module can cause a loss of audio signals, including safety sensor sounds, turn signals, and hazard signals, which can lead to accidents or near-misses, especially when driving on highways.
symptoms: The audio system malfunctions
losing sound or producing sudden loud sounds
the key fob and vehicle unit lose communication
warnings appear during driving
the vehicle experiences non-start issues
the failure occurs randomly and intermittently.
